'''The John P. Hussman Institute for Human Genomics''' (HIHG) was established at the [[University of Miami Miller School of Medicine]] in January 2007 to discover the genetic influences on human health and apply this knowledge to medical practice. It is listed as one of the top 20 genome centres by [[DNA sequencing]] capacity.<ref>{{cite web|last=Loman|first=Nick|title=Genomics: High-throughput "Next-Generation" Sequencing Facilities Statistics|url=http://pathogenomics.bham.ac.uk/hts/stats|accessdate=12 May 2011}}</ref> It is named after [[hedge fund]] owner, [[John Hussman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hussmanautism.org/team/hussman-john-p-ph-d-ms-ed/|title=John P. Hussman, Ph.D., MS.Ed|publisher=Hussman Foundation|date=2018}}</ref>
